@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam stateBorderColor #333
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam stateFontSize 12
skinparam arrowColor #666
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEFCE8
skinparam noteBorderColor #CCC

title **FR-02: Enrollment — State Diagram**\n<size:10>Student enrollment lifecycle</size>

state "ACTIVE" as active #C8E6C9 {
  active : status = "ACTIVE"
  active : Student is enrolled
  active :  and participating
}

state "DROPPED" as dropped #FFCDD2 {
  dropped : status = "DROPPED"
  dropped : Student removed
  dropped :  from course
}

[*] --> active : **Student registration**\nredeem_student_invite()\n→ _ensure_student_enrollment()\nINSERT enrollment(status=ACTIVE)

[*] --> active : **Join course**\nredeem_student_join_course()\n→ _ensure_student_enrollment()\nINSERT enrollment(status=ACTIVE)

active --> dropped : **Teacher removes student**\nDELETE /courses/{id}/students/{sid}\ncourses/views.remove_student()\nSET status = DROPPED

note right of active
  **Duplicate enrollment prevention:**
  UNIQUE(course_id, student_profile_id)
  constraint at database level.

  If student redeems a code for a
  course they're already enrolled in:
  - redeem_student_invite() raises
    ValueError("Student already enrolled")
  - redeem_student_join_course() returns
    (enrollment, already_enrolled=True)
    without consuming the code
end note

note right of dropped
  **No re-enrollment path** in current
  codebase. The unique constraint on
  (course, student_profile) means a
  new enrollment INSERT would violate
  the constraint. Re-enrollment would
  require updating the existing
  DROPPED record back to ACTIVE.
end note

@enduml
